ep my actual question intact, but please also surface things I didn't know to ask about, including:**\n\n1. **What \"tiny house\" actually means in Portland law.** I've heard the term used loosely \u2014 please tell me which legal categories my project could fall into and how they differ in plain English, including:\n   - A tiny house **on a permanent foundation** treated as a primary house or as an **Accessory Dwelling Unit (ADU)** / **Detached Accessory Dwelling Unit (DADU)**.\n   - A tiny house **on wheels** (like a park-model RV or THOW) and where Portland does or doesn't allow those to be lived in full-time.\n   - A **second house** on the same lot vs. replacing what's there vs. adding to what's there.\n   - Whether I can rent it out, live in it myself, or use it for family.\n\n2. **What zoning my address actually has and what that means for me.** Please look up or tell me how to look up the zoning for **831 SE 174th Ave** on **PortlandMaps (portlandmaps.com)**, and explain in plain English what that zone (likely something in the **R-zone** family in outer East Portland) lets me do, including:\n   - Whether a tiny house / ADU is allowed by right or needs special review.\n   - **Overlay zones** (extra rules layered on top of base zoning) that often catch people off guard \u2014 environmental, flood, landslide hazard, historic, design, plan district. East Portland near 174th sometimes has flood or environmental overlays near Johnson Creek and similar \u2014 flag if any apply.\n   - Lot size, lot width, and how much of the lot I'm allowed to cover with buildings.\n   - **How far the new building has to sit from each property line** (front, back, side) \u2014 explain \"setback\" in plain English.\n   - **How tall** the tiny house can be.\n   - Whether I need to keep a certain amount of the yard open or unpaved.\n\n3. **All the permits and reviews I might need, and what triggers each one.** Don't just list them \u2014 tell me what each one is for in one sentence. At