wer (Title 17 / BES rules):** Will I trigger stormwater management requirements? Sewer connection fees?\n- **Building, plumbing, electrical, mechanical (Titles 24, 25, 26, 27):** What permits will I need, and in what order?\n- **Floor area, FAR, or density bonuses** that apply to ADUs in Portland?\n- **Parking:** Are there parking requirements for an ADU at this address?\n- **Short-term rental rules** if I ever wanted to use it as one \u2014 what are the constraints?\n- **System Development Charges (SDCs):** Are there current SDC waivers or reductions for ADUs?\n\n**4. Permits and process**\n- What permit types are required (zoning permit, building permit, plumbing/electrical/mechanical sub-permits, sewer/water connection)?\n- What triggers each permit, and which can be combined?\n- Is there pre-application or early assistance available, and would you recommend it for my situation?\n- Typical **timeline** from application to approval to final inspection?\n- Typical **cost ranges** for permits + SDCs in Portland for an ADU (ballpark)?\n\n**5. Sequencing \u2014 what order should I do things?**\nPlease give me a clear, numbered list of the next steps in the order I should take them, starting from \"today\" \u2014 including which bureau or office to contact at each step (BDS, BPS, BES, PBOT, Urban Forestry, etc.) and which forms or online tools to use.\n\n**6. Common gotchas in Portland**\n- What are the most common mistakes Portland homeowners make when building an ADU (e.g., siting near property lines, missing tree review, sewer lateral surprises, height calculations on sloped lots)?\n- Anything specific to SE Portland / older neighborhoods (e.g., legacy lots, nonconforming structures, narrow lots) that I should watch for?\n\n**7. Accuracy caveats**\n- Please flag any answers where the **specific zoning, overlays, or constraints for 5112 SE Belmont St may differ** from your general answer, and tell me exactly where to verify (PortlandMaps.com, BDS counter, etc.).\n- N