ime waiting on irrelevant records.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Numbered checklist \u2014 start today\n\n1. **Today (15 minutes, free):** Open portlandmaps.com \u2192 search \"1719 SE Ladd Ave\" \u2192 click Permits, then Permits/Land Use/Code Enforcement \u2192 Historic Plumbing \u2192 and Utilities \u2192 Sewer Assets. Save/screenshot anything relevant. Confirm the 6 permits I listed match what you see.\n2. **Today (5 minutes, free):** Open heritagedata.prd.state.or.us/historic \u2192 search Portland, \"Ladd Ave,\" 1719 \u2192 review the H.R. North Residence record (#49624). This gives you the architectural description and contributing-status rationale.\n3. **Today (free):** Click the \"Historic Permits\" panel on PortlandMaps. If anything appears that wasn't in my 6-permit list, that's pre-database trade-permit cards; screenshot/download. (If nothing's there, that's also informative.)\n4. **This week (free, useful):** Schedule a **free 15-minute appointment with a PP&D planner** (portland.gov/ppd \u2192 \"schedule appointment\") if any renovation is on your mind. Bring screenshots from steps 1\u20133.\n5. **This week ($8 + GovQA account):** If steps 1\u20133 didn't surface what you need, file a public records request via portlandor.govqa.us. Recommended request narrative for your property:\n\n   > Property: 1719 SE Ladd Ave, Portland OR 97214 (Tax Account R200340 / State ID 1S1E02CA 03100). Please provide all retained permit records, drawings, plans, inspection notes, and trade-permit cards for this address from inception to present, with priority on any pre-2004 records not visible on PortlandMaps. Specifically include: (a) any retained Building, Plumbing, Electrical, or Mechanical permits or cards; (b) plans and inspection records associated with permit IVR 2358693 (2004 water service, app 2004-020466-PT) since this predates the June 2012 PortlandMaps document scan window; (c) all records associated with voided permits IVR 3502923 (2014-197300-MT) and IVR 3504546 (2014-1989